Bloomberg: Microsoft is investigating whether organizations related to DeepSeek improperly obtained OpenAI data. 
Citing people familiar with the matter, Bloomberg reported on Wednesday that Microsoft security researchers discovered last fall that individuals they believed might be associated with DeepSeek used the OpenAI application programming interface (API) to steal large amounts of data. 
OpenAI did not respond to Bloomberg's request for comment, and Microsoft declined to comment. DeepSeek and High-Flyer, a hedge fund founded by its founder Liang Wenfeng, have not yet responded to requests for comment by email.

Trump's AI Czar: DeepSeek's AI model uses distillation to learn from ChatGPT - The Wall Street Journal
David Sacks, U.S. President Trump's AI Czar, said on Tuesday that Chinese artificial intelligence company DeepSeek used OpenAI's content to train a new model that has taken the world by storm.
Sacks said he believes American artificial intelligence companies will take steps to try to protect their models from distillation. "It will definitely slow down the development of these copycat models," he said.
(There is a technique called "distillation" in artificial intelligence, which refers to the process by which one model learns from another model)

name: 李老师不是你老师

Some Chinese students have complained about overseas schools, websites, supermarkets, and stores using "Lunar New Year" to celebrate the Spring Festival, accusing them of discrimination and cultural appropriation.
A Chinese student organized hundreds of supporters to write a joint letter to accuse Durham University in the UK of using "Lunar New Year" to celebrate the New Year.
In recent years, mainland Chinese netizens have been arguing over which is the orthodox "Lunar New Year" and "Chinese New Year". Most believe that the Lunar New Year is exclusive to the Chinese, and that other Asian countries celebrating the Lunar New Year is "cultural appropriation."

The New York-based Southern Mongolian Human Rights Information Center issued a statement on the 27th saying that Hada, chairman of the Southern Mongolian Democratic League, has been officially nominated as a candidate for the 2025 Nobel Peace Prize. The nominees are four members of the Japanese Diet.
The statement said that Mr. Hada is a staunch human rights activist who has dedicated his life to protecting the rights of the Southern Mongolians, also known as Inner Mongolia in China. Over the past 30 years, he has suffered ruthless persecution, including an unjust arrest in 1995 and years of imprisonment and house arrest. Despite this, Mr. Hada continues to speak out for the rights of the Southern Mongolian people in a peaceful way.

In an internal email from the U.S. Navy, the Navy instructed all personnel not to download or install DeepSeek, nor to use it for any work-related or personal purposes.
The email stated that due to "potential security and ethical issues related to the source and use of the model", DeepSeek's AI should not be used "in any form".
A U.S. Navy spokesperson confirmed the authenticity of the email and said it was issued in accordance with the Navy Information Management Department's Generative Artificial Intelligence Policy.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
According to Reuters, Chinese artificial intelligence application DeepSeek appeared to be unavailable for download in Apple and Google app stores in Italy on Wednesday.
A notification displayed to users by Apple's App Store said the app was "currently not available in your country or region." A message on the Google Play Store said downloads were "not supported" in Italy. DeepSeek was still operating in other European countries and the United Kingdom on Wednesday.
The Italian Personal Data Protection Authority said, "Considering that the data of millions of people in Italy may be at high risk, the agency has asked the two companies and their affiliates to confirm what personal data is collected, the source of the data, the purpose, the legal basis, and whether the data is stored on servers located in China."
